entry.def: If you put one thing into another, you put the first thing inside the second.

example.ex: Combine the remaining ingredients and put them into a dish...
example.tran: 把剩下的配料调和好，放到一个盘子里。

example.ex: Until the 1980s almost all olives were packed into jars by hand.
example.tran: 直到 20 世纪 80 年代,几乎所有的橄榄都是手工装罐的。

entry.def: If you go into a place or vehicle, you move from being outside it to being inside it.

example.ex: I have no idea how he got into Iraq...
example.tran: 我不知道他是怎样进入伊拉克的。

example.ex: She got up and went into an inner office...
example.tran: 她站起来走进里间的办公室。

entry.tran: (打破或损坏表面而)进入,插入
entry.def: If one thing goes into another, the first thing moves from the outside to the inside of the second thing, by breaking or damaging the surface of it.

example.ex: Flavell had accidentally discharged a pistol, firing it into the ceiling...
example.tran: 弗拉维尔不小心扳动了一把手枪的扳机，子弹射入了天花板。

example.ex: The rider came off and the handlebar went into his neck.
example.tran: 骑车人从自行车上摔了下来,车把插进了他的脖子里。

entry.def: If one thing gets into another, the first thing enters the second and becomes part of it.

example.ex: Poisonous smoke had got into the water supply...
example.tran: 毒烟已经进入供水系统。

example.ex: The money went into a common fund.
example.tran: 这笔钱被放到了一个普通基金里。

entry.def: If you are walking or driving a vehicle and you bump into something or crash into something, you hit it accidentally.

example.ex: A train plowed into the barrier at the end of the platform...
example.tran: 火车撞上了月台尽头的栅栏。

example.ex: Joanna heard him bump into the table and curse again.
example.tran: 乔安娜听见他撞到了桌子上，又骂骂咧咧的。

entry.def: When you get into a piece of clothing, you put it on.

example.ex: She could change into a different outfit in two minutes...
example.tran: 她能在两分钟内换上一套不同的行头。

example.ex: He put on his underwear and got into his suit.
example.tran: 他穿好内衣,然后穿上西装。

entry.def: If someone or something gets into a particular state, they start being in that state.

example.ex: He had too much time on his hands and that caused him to get into trouble...
example.tran: 他手头时间太富裕了,反倒为他惹来了麻烦。

example.ex: I slid into a depression.
example.tran: 我逐渐消沉了。

entry.def: If you talk someone into doing something, you persuade them to do it.

example.ex: Gerome tried to talk her into taking an apartment in Paris.
example.tran: 杰罗姆试图说服她在巴黎买一套公寓。

entry.def: If something changes into something else, it then has a new form, shape, or nature.

example.ex: ...his attempt to turn a nasty episode into a joke.
example.tran: 他想把一段很不愉快的插曲变成一则笑话的尝试

example.ex: ...learning what she needs to know to grow into a competent adult.
example.tran: 学习那些要想成为真正意义上的成年人她必须知道的东西

entry.def: If something is cut or split into a number of pieces or sections, it is divided so that it becomes several smaller pieces or sections.

example.ex: Sixteen teams are taking part, divided into four groups...
example.tran: 有16个队参加,分为4组。

example.ex: Roll out the pastry and cut into narrow strips...
example.tran: 把油酥面团擀薄然后切成长条。

entry.def: An investigation into a subject or event is concerned with that subject or event.

example.ex: The concert will raise funds for research into Aids...
example.tran: 这场音乐会将为艾滋病研究筹集资金。

example.ex: We are beginning to have some insight into drug therapy.
example.tran: 我们开始对药物治疗有了一些深入了解。

entry.tran: 进入,转向(某一职业、行业)
entry.def: If you move or go into a particular career or business, you start working in it.

example.ex: In the early 1990s, it was easy to get into the rental business...
example.tran: 20 世纪 90 年代早期,进入租赁行业很容易。

example.ex: He closed down the business and went into politics.
example.tran: 他关闭公司投身政治。

entry.def: If something continues into a period of time, it continues until after that period of time has begun.

example.ex: He had three children, and lived on into his sixties...
example.tran: 他有3个孩子,已经60多岁了。

example.ex: The Open Golf Championship will be getting into its second day in a few hours.
example.tran: 再过几个小时,高尔夫公开锦标赛将进入第二天的比赛。

entry.def: If you are very interested in something and like it very much, you can say that you are into it.

example.ex: I'm into electronics myself.
example.tran: 我本身对电子很感兴趣。

list.explanation: somebody严厉批评、责骂或口头攻击(某人)

example.en: I don't know why she tore into me. I was at work when the window was broken.
example.zh: 我不明白她为什么冲着我发火。我上班时，那扇窗已经是破的了。

list.explanation: (something) 开始津津有味地吃(某物)

example.en: Jimmy tore into the turkey leg and cleaned it off in no time.
example.zh: 吉米开始津津有味地吃那火鸡腿，不一会儿就把它吃光了。

list.explanation: (some place)匆匆、急急忙忙进入(某处)

example.en: I tore into the office and answered the phone.
example.zh: 我急急忙忙地奔进办公室，接听电店。

list.explanation: 对某事发生兴趣，迷上某事物

example.en: I got into computers when I was in junior high school.
example.zh: 我念初中时就迷上计算机了。

example.en: When did you get into foreign films?
example.zh: 你什么时候迷上外国电影的？

list.explanation: 同意或答应干某事，(开始)认真处理、紧紧抓住某事

example.en: I can't wait to get my teeth into that Wallace job.
example.zh: 我想尽快接手华莱士干的那份差事。

example.en: Here. Sink your teeth into this and see if you can manage this project.
example.zh: 现在，开始好好十这事吧，者看你是否能够完成这个计划。

example.en: Oh，what you said! I'm breaking out into assholes? No!
example.zh: 啊，你说什么!我心惊胆战？不!
